Field Detail

NONVIABLE

public static WorkItem.State NONVIABLE
Indicates that the WorkItem is in an unusable state. Usually a WorkItem does not get delivered in this state or is only in this state temporarily.
The following scenarios might cause a WorkItem to be delivered in the nonviable state:
(1) A user has worked on a Session that contains a WorkItem with an active VoiceMediaInteraction, and that Session terminated abnormally through a process crash. The next time the user logs in, the user receives the WorkItem with the VoiceMediaInteraction in a nonviable state. The user can release the WorkItem.
(2) A User receives a new WorkItem that contains a VoiceMediaInteraction. Auto-accept is not enabled. Therefore, the WorkItem is only in the nonviable state temporarily, then the state changes to Alerting. This scenario is usually caused by a time lag after the server receives the call from the Telephony server and before the server receives the attributes of the call from the EDU server.
Nonviable is an exception state. You will only see a WorkItem in this state if there is a problem.

INITIATING

public static WorkItem.State INITIATING
Indicates that the workitem is being initiated by the user. This happens when the user makes a phone call.

ALERTING

public static WorkItem.State ALERTING
Indicates that the workitem is waiting for user acceptance. In a system with RONA enabled a workitem that is not accepted in the configured timeout period will be removed from the users worklist

DEFERRED

public static WorkItem.State DEFERRED
Indicates that the workitem will not be actively worked on by the user. A workitem may be deferred by the user or by the system

WORKING

public static WorkItem.State WORKING
Indicates that the workitem is currently being worked on by the user

PAUSED

public static WorkItem.State PAUSED
Indicates that workitem has been suspended. This would happen when some other workitem in the users worklist is made current. It is not possible to pause a workitem which has an active voice media interaction

WRAPUP

public static WorkItem.State WRAPUP
Indicates that the workitem has been released. Any wrapup related activity may be performed by the user at this point

CONFERENCING

public static WorkItem.State CONFERENCING
Indicates that a conference has been initiated on the workitem

CONSULTING

public static WorkItem.State CONSULTING
Indicates that a consult has been initiated on the workitem

TRANSFERRING

public static WorkItem.State TRANSFERRING
Indicates that the transfer has been initiated on the workitem
